---
title: One-Pot Shrimp & Bean Soup with Kale & Carrot
description: The best kind of soup? One made in a single pot that cooks up delicious flavor in just 20 minutes. This one does just that. Meaty Italian chicken sausage, kale, and carrot are simmered together in a rich, gently creamy chicken stock, and then cannellini beans are stirred in for even more hearty flavor. Even though it's super-satisfying, you won't be able to resist another spoonful.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/webimage-HFRC-R15562APU01_Hero_20MmCreamyChickenSausageWhiteBeanAndKaleSoupWithGarlicBread_W43-105-2025-2078c0e8.png
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67914a37d0643436c3263aea-en-US.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-shrimp-and-bean-soup-67914a37d0643436c3263aea
time required: 20m
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 550 kcal
  fat: 19 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 54 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 15 g
  sodium: 2440 mg
---

Wash and dry produce. Trim, peel, and halve @carrot{3%ounce} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; chop into bite-size pieces. Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1%can}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large #pot{} over medium heat. Add @chicken sausage{4%ounce}; using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces, then add carrot, kale, and @salt{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings). Cook, stirring occasionally, until sausage is cooked through, carrot is slightly softened, and kale begins to wilt, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Swap in shrimp for sausage (no need to break up meat into pieces!).

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @cornstarch{1%tbsp} with @water{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until mixture is smooth and no lumps remain.

> TIP: Mix with your finger to ensure there are no lumps!

Stir @chicken stock concentrate{2}, cornstarch mixture, half the beans, and @water{1 1/2%cups} (3 cups for 4) into pot with sausage and veggies. Using the back of a #wooden spoon{} or spatula, partially mash beans in pot.

Cover and bring to a boil, then immediately reduce to a low simmer. Cook until kale is wilted and broth has thickened slightly, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Check if the kale is wilting evenly and stir occasionally if necessary.

Stir in @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, remaining beans, and a big squeeze of lemon juice. Cook until combined and warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{2%tsp} and @black pepper{1%tsp} to taste.

> TIP: Add another splash of water if you prefer a thinner broth.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.